# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('./current_data.csv', index_col=0, infer_datetime_format=True)
data['ds'] = pd.to_datetime(data.index, dayfirst=True)

# Sort the data by date (just to be sure)
data.sort_values(by='ds', inplace=True)

# Calculate month-on-month returns
data['monthly_return'] = data['portfolio_value'].pct_change() * 100  # Calculating returns as a percentage

# Drop the first row since it will have NaN for returns
data = data.dropna()

# Print the resulting DataFrame with month-on-month returns

from prophet import Prophet

df = pd.DataFrame()
df["ds"]=data['ds']
df["y"]=data['portfolio_value']

# Create and fit the Prophet model
model = Prophet(changepoint_prior_scale=0.009)
model.fit(df)

# Generate future dates for prediction (365 days into the future)
future = model.make_future_dataframe(periods=365)

# Make predictions
forecast = model.predict(future)

# # Plot the forecast
# fig = model.plot_components(forecast)
# plt.title("Portfolio Value Forecast")
# plt.xlabel("Date")
# plt.ylabel("Portfolio Value")
# plt.show()

fig2 = model.plot(forecast)
plt.title("Portfolio Value Forecast")
plt.figure(figsize=(40,8))
plt.show()

# # Get the forecasted values for the next year
forecasted_values = forecast[['ds', 'yhat', 'yhat_lower', 'yhat_upper']].tail(365)

# # Save the forecasted values to a CSV file
forecasted_values.to_csv('portfolio_forecast.csv', index=False)
